The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 May session for profit bill

 New Delhi, March 27: Parliament is likely to be reconvened from May 10 to bring a comprehensive bill to amend the Parliament (Prevention of Disqualification) Act of 1959 to redefine an office of profit and related aspects.

 The session will be on till May 23. Amendments to the Criminal Procedure Code, aimed mainly at protecting witnesses in heinous crimes, could also be passed. 

 A decision is expected to be taken on March 30 at a meeting of the cabinet committee of parliamentary affairs.

 Priya Ranjan Das Munshi, the parliamentary affairs minister, said after a meeting with the Prime Minister his priority would be the amendments on the office of profit. 




